# What Docker should NOT send to the build daemon as "context".
#
# Every `docker build` tars up the context dir (here the repo root, since compose
# uses `context: .`) and ships it to the daemon. Anything listed here is excluded:
# smaller context = faster builds, better cache hits, and no chance of a stray
# secret or 400MB of node_modules leaking into an image layer.

# VCS + CI metadata — never needed to compile a binary.
.git
.github
.gitignore

# The entire frontend: it has its own build pipeline and its node_modules dwarf
# the Go source. The Go images never touch web/.
web

# Go build artifacts produced on the host (the image rebuilds these itself).
bin
**/*.test

# Local-only files.
*.log
.env
**/.env.local
scratchpad
